{"id":"501","name":"Get Direct Link","tagline":"Retrieves a direct Dropbox link to your chosen Shortcut","icon":"ios12 c2846468607 g59794","latest":"941","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2>Get Direct Link</h2>\n<p>This Shortcut is useful for those who are building Shortcuts with dependencies. It will save your chosen shortcut to a folder called <em>/Shortcuts/Shared/</em> in your Dropbox, create a public link, and convert the link to a direct download link; removing Dropbox landing page.</p>\n<h3>Requirements</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Shortcuts App</li>\n<li>Dropbox</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Tips</h3>\n<p>Encode this direct link and drop it into the Shortcut URL Scheme to create a quick install for your users. Here's how it works.</p>\n<p><code>[URL] -&gt; (Direct Link)</code>  </p>\n<p><code>[URL Encode] -&gt; (Encode)</code>  </p>\n<p><code>[Set Variable] -&gt; (DirectLinkEncoded)</code>  </p>\n<p><code>[Text] -&gt; (Short Cut Name)</code>  </p>\n<p><code>[URL Encode] -&gt; (Encode)</code>  </p>\n<p><code>[Set Variable] -&gt; (ShortCutNameEncoded)</code>  </p>\n<p><code>[URL] -&gt; (shortcuts://import-workflow?url=(DirectLinkEncoded)&amp;name=(ShortcutNameEncoded))</code>  </p>\n<p><code>[Open URLs]</code></p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.3 - Oct. 25, 2018, 7:34 p.m.</strong></p><p>Fixed version issue, which always said there was an update. </p>"}